radiographic_examinations.findings: The base of the lungs are clear. The liver enhances homogeneously with no focal lesion. The kidneys contain several subcentimeter hypodensities bilaterally likely representing benign renal cysts. There is a 1.2 cm lymph node inferior to the pancreatic uncinate process in the RLQ. There is a thickened appendix measuring up to 1 cm with associated stranding of the periappendiceal fat.
